<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2193&amp;p=11032#p11032"><![CDATA[
Yeah. By default Recent Programs doesn't have a label because it doesn't correspond to any real folder from which to take name. You have to enter some text for the label.<br />BTW the purpose of the Recent Programs item is to show the recent (or frequent) programs in a submenu instead of in the main menu. If you delete the item the programs will show in the main menu.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Mon Feb 17, 2014 10:22 pm</p><hr />
