<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2193&amp;p=11031#p11031"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">GauravK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />There will be some item below Programs on the Customize Start Menu tab which does not have a Label. When the Label field is empty, it shows &lt;No Text&gt;. For example, you may have the &quot;Recent programs&quot; item added which might say &lt;No text&gt; because it has text no label by default.<br /></div>GauravK:<br /><br />That was an excellent example. Before I read your message, on my User (non-Administrator) account, the Customize Start Menu tab, in the left COLUMN PADDING column, Programs had only one item: Recent Programs. (The actual programs list, when I looked at my Classic Start Menu, had fifteen folders, two additional items not in a folder, and &lt;No Text&gt;.)<br /><br />And when I clicked on Recent Programs, and open Edit Menu Item (Recent programs), Label has &lt;No Text&gt;, and Link, Tip, and Icon are empty. I tried deleting &lt;No Text&gt;, and it deleted but as soon as I exit Edit Menu Item (Recent programs) --- either by x or by OK --- I saw a quick flash of &lt;No Text&gt; coming back. Alternatively, clicking on Restore Defaults also restored &lt;No Text&gt;.<br /><br />So I deleted Recent Programs. And then &lt;No Text&gt; was forced to disappear.<br /><br />Programs remained in the left COLUMN PADDING column, but now nothing is listed in it.<br /><br />My Programs list no longer ends with &lt;No Text&gt;.<br /><br />In short, I think the problem is fixed.<br /><br />Thank you very much.<br /><br />R.N. (Roger) Folsom<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=487">RNFolsom</a> — Mon Feb 17, 2014 10:10 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
